snippet.title: Moravia Road Cleanup // Greater Grace Shorts
snippet.description:
We love #Baltimore and we spent time yesterday cleaning up the road that leads to our church. We filled up about 18-20 bags 😅

We were made for community. Let’s pray that God would move in the hearts of the people of our city. He is the only one who can truly change our hearts and make them white as snow.

// Pray for the city today during our Day of Prayer.
#cleanup #whiteassnow #bmorechurch #ggwo #howwechurch #thatsalotoftrash #shorts

snippet.title: Women's Seminar 2022 Recap | Greater Grace Shorts
snippet.description:
Wowowowow!!! We were overflowing with stories and messages from so many amazing women. It’s hard to believe it’s already over. It has been an amazing weekend of restoration! We are closest with our Lord when we get on our knees and surrender ourselves to Him. He restores what the locust has eaten and brings us above and beyond our expectations.

Our hearts are full of gratitude to all the people behind the scenes who put this amazing seminar together. Shout out to @mr._souvlakiforesthill for an amazing lunch and some dangerously delicious baklavas.

#bmorechurch #ggwowomen #womenseminar #howwechurch #ggwo #restored

Minded and Marked to Serve | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Love slave to the Master is what Jesus came to be. He was pierced to be devoted to His Father’s will. We should have our minds conformed to His mind. This mind is not blown about and tricked by sleights and craftiness. (Philippians 2:5; Exodus 21:2, 5-6; Psalm 40:6; John 20:20)

Speaker: Justin Schaller, Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12578
6:30 PM on 09/10/2023

snippet.title: The Word and Worship | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Worship is about entering the courts of the Lord with praise and thanks. We follow after Him who worthy of praise and honor. All might and dominion is His. Psalm 63; Psalm 100:1-4

Speaker: Mark Miniciello, Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-09-03
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: Respond and Trust in the Will of God | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: The will of the Lord is something we should seek. Can we put our things before Him and hear His leading? There’s beauty and oil and garments of praise for us so we may glorify God.
Luke 22:41-43; Isaiah 61:3; 2 Samuel 5:17-24

Speaker: Chris Arman, Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12570
Date: 2023-08-27
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: It’s All by the Spirit | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: Do we realize what the Holy Spirit does in us and through us? More than power, the Spirit is Person. The Spirit connects us to the Bible, to grace, and to church. We bear fruit and grow in faith for He is the Spirit of the Gospel. Acts 1:7-8; Joshua 22:28

Speaker: Steven Scibelli, Roger Robbins
Sermon: 12566
Date: 2023-08-20
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: Changed to Walk in the Spirit | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The very one who rubs us the wrong way may be the one we need. The Spirit guides and fills us. We are changed through the Word and church life. Love leads and brings us together. Galatians 5:15-20

Speaker:  Thomas Schaller, Micah Stambovsky
Date: 2023-08-13
Time: Sun 6:30 PM

snippet.title: Patient Faith, Wise Contentment | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
God sent us into this world full of troubles. Whatever we face we have Him with us. Job learned this through all he endured. Faith, wisdom, contentment, and patience became the definition for him. (Job 1:6-12; James 1:1-8; Psalm 63:1-3)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Steve Andrulonis
Sermon 12558
6:30 PM on 08/6/2023

snippet.title: Our Know-So Hope | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Hope is born from belief. We hear Word and this brings desire and conviction. Abraham hoped when it was hopeless and Sarah conceived as an old lady. (Proverbs 13:12; Romans 10:13)

Speaker: Eric Handel, Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12554
6:30 PM on 07/30/2023

snippet.title: The Loyal Love of the Lord | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Loyal love is behind all that God in His commitment and covenants — both unconditional and conditional ones. He never gives up even in His people’s disobedience. Joel reveals God’s message to call people back His way. We see His promise and His persistent love. (Joel 2:12-31; 3:2; Genesis 12:2-3; Deuteronomy 28:3, 15-19)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-07-23
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: The Virtue of Hope | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Faith and hope operate on our trust in God. We wait in our salvation with full confidence. Even in our wilderness, God gives a door of Hope. Our comfort is in the Amen of Finished Work and the Resurrection. To live without spiritual hope is to live in defeat. (Hosea 2:14-16; Ephesians 2:12-13)

Speaker: Kim Shibley, Glenn Cannon
Sermon 12546
6:30 PM on 07/16/2023

snippet.title: God-Taught for Love and Mission | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Church life is what brings us to enjoy the poured out love from Him. Lord leads us to have glory in quiet life and in minding our own business. (1 Thessalonians 4:9-12)

Speaker: Mark Miniciello, Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12542
6:30 PM on 07/09/2023

snippet.title: Brothers, Workers, Soldiers and Ministers | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: Examples of faith with likeminded character stir us in purpose of care. Paul, Timothy, and Epaphroditus demonstrate the way of the walk in Him. We are eager for the success of others. Philippians 1:29-2:1-5, 17-27; John 17:3

Speaker: Justin Schaller, Jean Cartier
Sermon 12534
6:30 PM on 06-25/2023

snippet.title: The Feet of Jesus and the Heart of God | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
In the heart of God, things that do not exist already exist. Sit at His feet as Mary did. Everything will be under those feet. He speaks things and He cares to correct in mercy. David learned the way of His presence and His heart. (Psalm 103:13-14; 2 Samuel 6:9)

Speaker: Chris Arman, Matti Sirvio, Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-06-18
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: We Belong to Something More | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
God has called us to tell the Gospel. Healthy spiritual life helps this happen as it grows in church context. Gifts find room to operate and expand the work of Heaven. (Ephesians 4:11-23)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-06-11
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: Corporate Body Guidance | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
In church life, we learn the way of the Spirit. It can messy at moments. We let the love of God flow even to enemies. Corporate life encourages obedience as there is accord led by leaders who have hazarded their lives in Christ. (1 Samuel 5:1-6; Luke 6:26-27; Acts 15:24-29)

Speaker(s): Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12522
6:30 PM on 6/4/2023

snippet.title: Be Spirit-Filled and Build | SUN 6:30P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Caleb was man with the right spirit after God. He stood on the promise of the Lord regarding the land. His heart desires the victory he believed was coming. Flesh can be self-righteous and judgmental. Flesh also has a poor memory. (Numbers 13:28-14:11; 11:5)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-05-28
Time: Sun 6:30pm

snippet.title: Changed Concepts by Spirit, Word and Love | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Our culture bombards us with ideas and concepts. We need an understanding of God and His kindness and His serious severity. By the Holy Spirit and the Word, we see the holiness of our true God. People are given; these are church leaders and members to help us see Him. He has ordained His means to help our growth and expansion. (Ephesians 4:11-15)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Gary Groenewold
Sermon: 12577
11:00 AM on 09/10/2023

snippet.title: Searched and Known, Responding in Faith  | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The sense of God’s presence can come and go. And yet He is with us. We can bring ourselves to Him and be searched by Him. Think His thoughts. Just a seed of faith can make a difference. (Psalm 139; Isaiah 54:7-8; Mark 7:31-37)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12573
11:00 AM on 09/3/2023

snippet.title: Carried by Joy in this Troubled World | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Have you lost anything? Of course, you have. Jesus brought losers to Him. He is such as these; He is for us. He makes us new for His wine and for His new cloth. By grace, He carries us.
Psalm 30:5-11; Mark 2:15-22

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Barry Quirk
Sermon: 12569
Date: 2023-08-27
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Approach the Lord, Give Thanks, Receive Power | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: Our world is dark ruled by the devil with a pretend peace and love. We need more. Jesus made a way of approach God and we do it with boldness. It’s a gift that brings power. Be thankful with joy and gladness for this. Hebrews 10:19; 2 Kings 4:30-36; Psalm 100:1-5

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Mat Gehret
Date: 2023-08-20
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Live Light and Easy, Full of the Spirit | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Our flesh, our sin nature, remains with us. That part of us cannot be fed. We walk in the Holy Spirit and in hatred, variance, and emulation. Live rather in peace, the Word, and church life. Galatians 5:13-21

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-08-13
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Our High Rock Who Cares | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Jesus was a man of sorrows. He cared and had compassion. He sets us on the Rock of Truth. We are taken above self and we are sent to tell of Him who has written our names in the Book of Life. Ask, seek, and knock — He will answer and give. (Luke 10:1-22; Psalm 61:1-2)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12557
11:00 AM on 08/6/2023

snippet.title: God's Story of Patience | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12553
11:00 AM on 07/30/2023

snippet.title: Armor for the Night | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Darkness has its power. Even Jesus had to stop talking and face the night. Christ died, but then He rose. The hour of evil is limited. It shall end. He gives us His armor and so we stand with His strength. (Luke 4:18-30; 22:52-53; John 14:30; Ephesians 6:10-18)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Eugene Davis
Date: 2023-07-23
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Small Things Do Count with Jesus | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Mustard seed and leaven are such small things. Jesus uses these to illustrate how faith makes a difference. Slings and sticks and string and needles, loaves, fishes — small stuff made great by God serves Him and reveals His power. (Matthew 13:31-34)

Speaker: John Love
Sermon 12545
11:00 AM on 07/16/2023

snippet.title: Decree and Victory, Rejoicing and Trembling | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
People sought unity in their own name. God used this to bring languages and scatter men and then came the call of Abraham. Still, vanity rules and kings seek to break cords of God and the Messiah. Heaven’s plan proceeds, however, according to His decree and the victory of the Son begotten from death, seated now in majesty. The heathen become His in all parts.
Genesis 11:1-6; Psalm 2

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Jon Post
Date: 2023-07-09
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Our Justice Paid, We’re Free in His Name | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Jesus paid for sin. Justice required it. The Son was bruised. He was led away by evil hands. He was clothed with our shame and then crowned with thorns. He was mocked and spat upon. Now we are rich and blessed and honored because He was served justice. Mark 15:16-20; Isaiah 53:10

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-06-18
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Sound from the Word to Take to the World | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Paul, in Athens, addressed the lies and idols he saw. Culture tries to dominate and distracts. Millions are wrecked and need the Gospel. Living God talks to us and hears us. With the Word, we learn of Him and His mind. Acts 17:17-32; Psalm 1

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-06-11
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: Presence and Forgiveness, Head and Hands | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The Lord is great. People see all gods as the same. But Jesus and His Presence are different. Everything falls before Christ. The idol of the Philistines lost his head and hands before the Ark of God. Can we forgive and let go of resentment? (1 Samuel 5:1-5)

Speaker(s): Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12521
11:00 AM on 6/4/2023

snippet.title: Follow in the Spirit, Lose Yourself, Take the Cross | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Heart has a place only God can fill. Our hearts have serious issues. We need His love shed abroad by the Holy Spirit. Our fictions must be brought to the reality of the Lord. Trying to save your life is to really lose. Go to the Cross and gain all things. Psalm 73; Ezekiel 36:26; Matthew 16:24-25.

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-05-28
Time: Sun 11am

snippet.title: The Pull of the Call of Faith | SUN 11A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Abraham left his home and its idolatry in obedience. He chose to seek the City whose Builder and Maker is the Lord. Impossible and laughable things happened to him and to Sarah. His children became as the stars in the heavens. This man took heart and claimed the promise of Christ. (Hebrews 11:8-13)

Speaker(s): Thomas Schaller, Gary Groenewold
Sermon 12513
11:00 AM on 5/21/2023

snippet.title: Concepts of God and Self l Sun 9AM // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The average person has a big view or self and a small view of God. Through the grace of God and the Body of Christ, these concepts can be brought to order for a spiritual life. (Ephesians 4)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Gary Groenewold
Sermon: 12576
9:00 AM on 09/10/2023

snippet.title: Opened Ears, Loosed Tongue  | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Deaf and dumb man gets healed. All became open for him. God speaks to us and we are made to hear and talk for Him. We have His grace and victory. He is with us where we are. (Mark 7:31-37)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12572
9:00 AM on 09/3/2023

snippet.title: The One Thing Needed | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Young ruler came running to Jesus. He wanted an answer, but was stunned by what the Savior told him. (Mark 10:17-22)

Speaker: Mat Gehret, Barry Quirk
Sermon: 12568
Date: 2023-08-27
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: Live Before God in Connection | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
People strangely feel wearied by God. Our self life and others brings them down. We lack power because our relationship. We must choose to enter Tabernacle life and worship Him. Get Connect with the life in Trinity. Come before Him and sing. Psalm 100:1-4: 2 Kings 4:30-36; Micah 6:3

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Zane Turk
Date: 2023-08-20
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: Care and Prayer | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Jesus was a man of sorrows. He cared and had compassion. With prayer, our hearts reveal our care. Go beyond excuses and seek Him through love. Ask, seek, and knock — He will answer and give. (Isaiah 53:3; Luke 10:17-22; Luke 11:1-13)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12556
9:00 AM on 08/6/2023

snippet.title: The Unlimited Patient Love of God | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Fred Ellis
Sermon 12552
9:00 AM on 07/30/2023

snippet.title: Stand Strong in Hope | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Evil days come. Devil works in an hour of power. We have the armor of God to stand strong in Him and in His might. Take this armor and believe His Word. (Ephesians 6:10-13; John 4:47-54; 1 Corinthians 7;29-31)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-07-23
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: The Fire of Ultimate Grace | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Grace is always the answer. We need this every moment we feel like failures. Our gifts and callings are forever. He transforms us with His fire and burns away guilt and shame. John 1:14–18; John 21

Speaker: Mat Gehret
Date: 2023-07-16
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: The Name, Nations and Contentment | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Men seek an empty name and power. They are greedy for this. The Lord found friend in Abraham and those who live by faith. Such as these shall triumph in the Gospel over the deceived world by coming to the Savior. The begotten Son came out of death and sits in majesty. The heathen are His.
Genesis 35:18-19; Genesis 11:3-8; Psalm 2

Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Lenin Maxwell Stanley
Date: 2023-07-09
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: Positioned by Grace | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
God can be known. This comes by grace. Experience and feelings should not be elevated above the revelation of God. He gives grace for operation in His purpose in victory. (1 Peter 5:10-11; Romans 1:18-25)

Speaker: Steven Scibelli, Steve DeVries
Date: 2023-06-18
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: The Word Makes Him Known | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
How unique is the Word in our world? Our meditation on this Word makes the Lord and stirs us to pray. The true God can be known. Mission becomes a big part of our hearts. Acts 17:11-24

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-06-11
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: In His Presence, Idols Fall | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Encounter the presence and holiness of God and be changed. The Philistines out the Ark of God before their god Dagon. This image lost his head and hands. The presence of God can set us free the same way. (1 Samuel 5:1-6)

Speaker(s): Thomas Schaller, Steve Andrulonis
Sermon 12520
9:00 AM on 6/4/2023

snippet.title: Magnify the Heart of God | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
We can so disturbed about things. But we must magnify Christ. Let the Spirit stir the reality and power of the Body life in the Church. Philippians 1:20-26; Psalm 100

Speaker: James Dadidis
Date: 2023-05-28
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: Obey and See the Promises | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Abraham left his home and city in obedience. He knew God and came to seek the City whose Builder and Maker is the Lord. Impossible and laughable things happened to him and to Sarah. He seed became as the stars in the heavens. This man saw and claimed the promise of Christ. (Hebrews 11:8-13)

Speaker(s): Thomas Schaller, Gary Groenewold
Sermon 12512
9:00 AM on 5/21/2023

snippet.title: Be Holy: Know It and Show It | SUN 9A // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Holiness is ours by the Cross. Jesus sold all He had to give us true riches. The young ruler had everything and lived along the lines of the Law. He was still needy. Mark 10:17-22; Isaiah 66:13

Speaker: Steve Andrulonis, Cedric Tanksley
Date: 2023-05-14
Time: Sun 9am

snippet.title: Alive From the Inside  | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The woman taken in adultery had everything against her on the outside. She was caught and guilty. But Jesus saw the inside. He brought beauty and said, “Neither do I condemn you.” Come to God in fellowship and get the ministry that’s needed. John 8; Psalm 27:4; James 4:10-11

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-09-06
Time: Wed 7:30pm

snippet.title: The Son and the World to Come | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: True and faithful words tell us about what is to come. Jesus came as the Son to what He made and to what He is heir to. People in Heaven watch and wait to see Christ in triumph, as they live in presence of God. Cries and questions go up. Revelation 6:9-11; 21:5; Hebrews 1:1-5; 2:15-17; Psalm 8:1-5

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12571
Date: 2023-08-30
Time: Wed 7:00pm

snippet.title: Come Away, Have Joy, Seek Forgiveness | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The Voice of God is there and meets us. There are bad times and walls.
We can be imprisoned by feelings and hurts. We hear to get through in our need and on to the days of singing. Song of Solomon 2:8-10; Matthew 5:23-25; 2 Kings 4:19-26

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon: 12567
Date: 2023-08-23
Time: Wed 7:00pm

snippet.title: The Tabernacle Way to Pray | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: The way of coming to God is shown in the picture of the Tabernacle. We can go to the Mercy Seat of grace. Take time as you go to Him. Start with thanks at the gate and enter the courts. Confession comes at the altar. The brass laver holds water to wash and we are made clean by the engrafted Word and Spirit. Eat at the table and rest in the fragrance of incense and light of the lamp that pictures church life.
Hebrews 10:19-20; Psalm 100:1-4


Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-08-16
Time: Wed 7PM

snippet.title: Heads, Not Tails | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Lives of preparation are revealed in crises. Joseph had the interpretation and the plan to save an empire and his small family. He opened the storehouses to feed the people. We are not tails, we are given headship. We have changed life. We bring peace and kindness. (Deuteronomy 28:13-14; Genesis 41:51-56; Ephesians 4:23-32; Philippians 3:5-7)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12559
7:00 PM on 08/9/2023

snippet.title: Hunger for God and Be Full | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description:  Hunger for God and Be Full
Description: First-floor life, the natural way of things, can grip us. We chase satisfaction and it eludes us. Vanity swallows the stuff. The loving kindness of God is better than all of it. Seek Him. Go to the upper level. Drop what you’re holding tightly. Be filled with His life. Be different and go hard after God.
Psalm 63

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12555
7:00 PM on 08/2/2023

snippet.title: Forsake All, Take the Cross and Follow | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Description: Jesus refused to seek popularly. He went on offense vs. the world. He asks this of us. He calls to self denial and the Cross life. He calls us to be disciples who make disciples. (Luke 2:47-52; Luke 4:20-28; Luke 14:26-38; Matthew 16:16-25)

Speaker: Peter Westera, Jesse Feyers. Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-07-26
Time: Wed 7:00pm

snippet.title: Justice, Forgiveness and Freedom | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Our debt of sin before God is incalculable. He has forgiven all in His mercy. But do we take this to heart and extend such mercy and release to others? This is the question that indicates just how much we appreciate His mercy. (Matthew 18:21-35)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-07-19
Time: Wed 7:30pm

snippet.title: Regard the Word and Have Joy | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
The people In Jerusalem stood and they were attentive to the reading of the Law of Moses. Weeping was the first result. But the Word stirred rejoicing. Read, hear and realize who God is. (Nehemiah 8:1-3, 7-10; 1 Corinthians 7:9-10)

Speaker: Dennis White
Sermon 12543
7:00 PM on 07/12/2023

snippet.title: Fully Covered & Enjoying Faith Rest | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Speaker: Thomas Schaller, Barry Quirk
Sermon 12539
7:00 PM on 07/05/2023

snippet.title: Don’t Linger, Seek God, Follow After Him | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Lot, like many, find themselves in the wrong place, vexed by the atmosphere such as was in Sodom. He lingered. He had to be pulled away by angels. He needed help. It was mercy. Seek Him. Follow after God. Don’t linger in sin. Don’t look behind. Go forward. (Genesis 19:1-26; Song 3:1-4)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12535
7:00 PM on 06/28/2023

snippet.title: The Voice, Our Obedience and the Lamb | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Leprosy from world infects, Voice of God heals and resurrects. Abraham heard and obeyed. He listened and understood who spoke to Him. Service under the Lamb. His Blood makes us clean. (2 Kings 4; Genesis 22:1-2; Romans 12:1)

Speaker(s): Michel Texier, Bensku Hollopainan, Ryan Raina
Sermon 12527
7:00 PM on 6/14/2023

snippet.title: Gifts by Measure for His Body | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
God measures out His gifts to those who believe upon Him. By these gifts, His Church is formed and made to thrive. The gifts serve to bring us together and grow in community that operates in love. (Ephesians 4:7-11; Daniel 2:44-45; 7:14–15; John 3:34)

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Date: 2023-05-31
Time: Wed 7:30pm

snippet.title: Lines in Pleasant, Joyful Places | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Jesus speaks to put His joy in you. This remains in us. Branch in the Vine must bear fruit. Let His peace reign. Set the Lord before your face and be immoveable. John 15:11; Psalm 16:5-10

Speaker: Thomas Schaller
Sermon 12515
7:00 PM on 5/24/2023

snippet.title: She Really Touched Jesus | WED 7P // Greater Grace Church
snippet.description:
Woman with the issue of blood crawled through the crowd. She touched the hem of Jesus’ garment. She stopped God. It was a healing and deliverance. For the rest of her days, she celebrated. Those 12 years of affliction did so much for her and for those who read about her. (Luke 8:42-46)

Speaker(s): Peter Westera
Sermon 12511
7:00 PM on 5/17/2023
